## MONGODB — KEY RULES

Profile is a singleton. Always use:
Profile.findOneAndUpdate({}, payload, { upsert: true, new: true })
The empty {} filter is intentional — always matches the one doc.

TTL indexes — create both once on DB connect in db.ts:
- jobs:      { fetchedAt: 1 },   { expireAfterSeconds: 21600 }   // 6h
- searches:  { computedAt: 1 },  { expireAfterSeconds: 86400 }   // 24h

Bookmarks must store title, company, externalUrl directly on the document —
not just a jobRef — because jobs expire every 6h and get deleted.
Always denormalize these fields so the tracker never breaks.

---

## GEMINI — KEY RULES

- Model: gemini-1.5-flash only. Never use pro, ultra, or any other model.
- Temperature: 0.3 — non-negotiable, keeps JSON output consistent
- maxOutputTokens: 2048
- All Gemini calls go through gemini.service.ts only
- Never call the Gemini SDK directly from a route file
- Strip ```json fences before JSON.parse — Gemini sometimes adds them anyway
- On JSON.parse failure: log the raw string, throw { code: 'GEMINI_PARSE_ERROR', raw }
- Never crash the process on a Gemini parse failure

---

## CACHE — KEY RULES

Cache key = SHA256(chainType + JSON.stringify(inputs))
Check Search collection before every single Gemini call.
Enforce TTL in code by checking computedAt age in milliseconds:
- context:  1h  — 3_600_000 ms
- jobScore: 6h  — 21_600_000 ms
- gigIdeas: 24h — 86_400_000 ms
- rates:    24h — 86_400_000 ms

